1 (7) The court may prohibit an offender convicted under this section from possession or use of the
2 firearm used in the assault. The court may enforce 45-8-323 if a firearm was used in the assault.
3 (8) The court shall provide an offender with a written copy of the offender's sentence at the time of
4 sentencing or within 2 weeks of sentencing if the copy is sent electronically or by mail.
5 (9) A victim may not be charged with partner or family member assault.
6 (10) Only one party to a partner or family member assault incident may be charged with partner or
